# 5. 力になりたい

Kanade: (So many people...)
Kanade: (It's incredible how they're all able to withstand this cold weather.)
Saki: Kanade?
Kanade: Oh... Sorry, it's nothing.
Kanade: So, where are we going today again?
Saki: This new makeup lounge that opened just recently!
Saki: I want to test out some things before our shoot, so... Oh, this is it!
Kanade: It's so glittery...
Saki: Isn't this place incredible?! You can try out all the cosmetics you want for one hour with just one coin♪
Kanade: Wow, I honestly had no idea that a place like this existed...
Kanade: ...
Saki: Is something the matter?
Kanade: Oh, it's just... Now I sort of wish there was a place where you could freely try out musical instruments and equipment.
Saki: Yeah! Most shops will let you if you ask the staff, but you only ever get to play for a few minutes.
Kanade: Right. However, I may just be uninformed. An instrument lounge like that may already exist...
Saki: You have me curious now! Let's look that up later!
Saki: <And guess what? Mizuki and Shizuku agreed to lend me some of their clothes too!>
Kanade: <They did? Yes, those two do both seem to have extensive wardrobes.>
Saki: <Exactly! They really saved the day since they had just the kinds of clothes I was hoping to use!>
Saki: <Anyway, now I know what I'm going to have you wear...>
Saki: <Which brings me to...! Our special guest!>
Kanade: <Special guest?>
Saki: <That's right! She's one of my friends from school, and she agreed to help out after I told her about my project.>
Saki: <So, without further ado, from all the way in the United States, it's... Kohane!>
Kohane's Voice: <H-Hello...!>
Kohane: <Umm... Can you two see me okay?>
Saki: <Yeah, we see you just fine!>
Kohane: <Hehe. Thank goodness.>
Kohane: <Hello, Yoisaki. Oh, wait a second... Maybe “good evening” is more appropriate based on what time it is in Japan right now...>
Kanade: <Umm... Hello. You perform in the same team as Ena's brother, yes?>
Kohane: <Yes, my name is Kohane Azusawa.>
Saki: <Kohane's a really amazing photographer!>
Saki: <So, today, I'm hoping to get as much advice from her as possible on taking good pictures!>
Kanade: <I see... Then, Azusawa, thank you for joining us.>
Kohane: <I-I'm really not as good as she makes me out to be...>
Kohane: <But I will try to help in any way I can.>
Saki: <Thanks, Kohane! Then, I'll start by asking...>
Saki: <How do you take good portraits of people?>
Kohane: <Portraits...?>
Kohane: <Well, I suppose it's important to choose a good location and a plan for bringing your subject's charm to the surface.>
Saki: <Yes, I see. Bring Kanade's charm to the surface somehow...>
Kohane: <Also, since your project already has a specific theme attached to it... You may want to find a way to factor that in somehow.>
Kanade: <Factor in the theme?>
Kohane: <Yes. When I entered into this photography contest for Valentine's Day a while back...>
Saki: <Thanks, Kohane! I have a much better idea of how to take the pictures I want now!>
Kanade: <Thank you for also going into detail regarding what a model needs to do during a shoot.>
Kohane: <I'm glad that I was able to help.>
Kohane: <Good luck, you two. I hope your project turns out really well!>
Saki: That was a great shoot!
Kanade: Great shoot to you as well, Tenma. We ended up taking quite a few pictures. Did any immediately stand out to you...?
Saki: Yes, you looked so amazing in every outfit that I'm having trouble deciding which picture to use!
Kanade: I see...
Saki: I printed them out, so could we take a look together?
Saki: This is also your chance to let me know if you see any that you don't want me to use.
Kanade: Okay, thank you.
Kanade: (I was worried that I'd made some funny faces since I'm not used to having my picture taken...)
Kanade: (But thank goodness. My expressions look more natural than I was expecting.)
Kanade: (I can't thank Azusawa enough for the advice she gave me. And Tenma did a good job of helping me relax during the shoot by talking to me...)
Kanade: *Nod* I've looked through all of them now, and I didn't see any problems.
Kanade: Which means, Tenma, all that's left is for you to choose...
Kanade: Tenma...?
Saki: Huh...? Oh, I'm sorry! Did you find any problems at all?!
Kanade: No, I didn't notice anything...
Kanade: Sorry, did they not turn out the way you hoped?
Saki: No, don't apologize! You did nothing wrong, Kanade!
Saki: It's just...
Saki: Umm... This is probably going to sound a little strange...
Saki: But something is missing. Do you know what I mean...?
Kanade: Missing?
Saki: Yes...
Kanade: (As far as I can see, nothing appears to be missing.)
Kanade: Is there something in particular that you're not happy with...?
Saki: Huh...?
Kanade: Oh, I'm sorry if I misspoke...
Kanade: This is just my gut feeling, but you seem to be hung up on something, Tenma...
Saki: ...
Saki: Hung up... That'd be an exaggeration...
Saki: It's just...
Saki: I feel like there's something I can do to make you even more radiant, you know...?
Kanade: Even more radiant...
Saki: Yes...
Saki: Take this picture for example. I chose this outfit with the goal of drawing out your mysterious side.
Saki: And this one was supposed to capture the kindness you showed when you helped us with our songs for Shibu Schools Fest...
Saki: They all have elements of the radiance I see in you... So, I don't know why I'm feeling this way.
Kanade: I see...
Kanade: (Tenma knows what she's trying to capture. If she still feels like there's something missing, then...)
Kanade: Could my inexperience as a model be the problem...?
Saki: No!
Saki: You really did do an amazing job, Kanade! You looked cool, cute and super duper ridiculously gorgeous in every picture!
Kanade: Th-Thank you...
Saki: No, not at all...!
Kanade: (That feeling of what you're trying to capture being just barely out of your grasp...)
Kanade: (Why does that seem so familiar...? I feel like I understand what she's going through.)
Kanade: (Oh...)
Kanade: (That's right... I experience the same thing sometimes when I'm composing a song.)
Kanade: (I'll have a message or theme solidly in mind but struggle to express it properly...)
Kanade: (A process of trial and error will produce a few possible solutions, but none will seem right...)
Kanade: (Tenma might be going through the same thing right now.)
Kanade: (Then, all I can do now is...)
Kanade: I understand...
Saki: Huh?
Kanade: This is just my guess... But I think you should trust your sense that something is missing.
Kanade: Because I'll find myself feeling the same way sometimes when I'm composing a song...
Saki: Kanade...
Kanade: So, I'm willing to continue helping you until you've taken a picture that captures what you feel is missing.
Saki: What...?! A-Are you sure?!
Kanade: Yes. You still have time until you have to turn in your project...
Kanade: I agreed to help you... So I want to see this through until the end.
Saki: Kanade... Thank you so much.
Saki: If you'll bear with me for just a bit longer!
Kanade: *Nod* Let's do our best, Tenma...
